[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing workflow dependencies**\n\nI’m looking at the workflow setup and considering what dependencies we need before the generation phase. Maybe including `boot-autoconfigure` and `boot-test` would be useful, and possibly `spring-boot-actuator` for actuator endpoints. I wonder if we can get meaningful library coverage without it, though the core quartz scheduler might suffice. I should clarify if more deterministic dependencies are needed for adequate coverage, ensuring we avoid conflicts and are aligned with local artifacts. Then, maybe I'll consider system properties for Quartz.\n\n**Investigating Quartz scheduler requirements**\n\nI'm looking into how the Quartz default scheduler behaves, especially regarding non-daemon threads. It seems important to either shut down the scheduler in tests or close the context runner properly. Guidance might suggest keeping the in-memory job store and avoiding JDBC unless an embedded DataSource is added. I should check about the update check property too, `org.quartz.scheduler.skipUpdateCheck=true`, to see if it's really necessary. Finally, I need to confirm if I should prefer `spring-boot-starter` over `spring-boot-autoconfigure` for dependencies.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04e9419ef8ccb5e1016a3fe49096d881958125856a30bd41ed\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP-SX8BY-JoEj5UOnqMj4W4tjDbpohGi36qo2Ei-wiI5WBU55nLp3AsqB8UBG-jOLrYwy1hGAN8F2sAF3Ks9mArsPgbyLgjdPy5EL-frwHg3k2TgIoe3zbN6MpRmI6KtckzUh9Tz29LYH-MIeU_aCGQ3WswRRgE3kOJ-STZuVDxn2PIq6-lHm89sPQeJXDHFwDTiKSDvup-7ELVuWuGo2cKChAp9wd8MPyWsAKa2A1oPlYEUWl8ucoNsPPXBnVP1htc3dzEpOj66zDfxfrOQBr0S7hOKI4JNnWTwBefW8x_JMPAoGBUIxD0LAU2-CjJC3Gd7dHj6W3W2AaU4dv0QzZVVt-8F5MHQzQY_FluJ1RIezrJotujYGSLnJ-3--40RR7O3aZFiUSvQCK26mIjhszx7ZwA0USFzaaOAg5gQW77XtBCw7CPpc0aE2Ybmvscc0Y_y91PJwnBSY0DkC5P2NlDZ4cAJZQqs1JdZSMM362GAXen8kMLAcjlobzSzoz1AqXk1eAI-OivDX