de `spring.quartz.auto-startup=false` to prevent actual scheduler threads from running, although it might be useful for meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage and context management**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how generated tests might fail if the context isn't closed properly, so I need to provide guidance. Setting `spring.quartz.auto-startup=false` seems like a good option, but I worry it might reduce coverage. I want to make sure I'm helping the user understand the balance between managing context and getting the most coverage possible. It's all about finding that sweet spot, right? Let’s ensure the tests run effectively without unnecessary complications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating risk notes**\\n\\nI need to mention the optional actuator in the context of risks. The artifact contains actuator endpoint classes, and I think endpoint-specific coverage would require spring-boot-actuator. However, it's not strictly necessary for the core scheduler. I’m wondering if this \\\"risk note\\\" I'm outlining is sufficient or if it needs further detail to be more comprehensive. Let’s see how I can clarify this point moving forward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Spring Boot's Quartz support is normally exercised as Boot auto-configuration; the resolved artifact brings Quartz and Spring context support but not Boot auto-configuration/test support used for meaningful context-based coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact contains QuartzAutoConfiguration and related auto-configuration classes, but its resolved dependencies do not include the core Boot auto-configuration APIs needed to exercise them in the normal Spring Boot style.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Spring Boot auto-configuration modules are typically tested with ApplicationContextRunner, which is provided by spring-boot-test and gives meaningful lightweight coverage without launching a full application.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use the default in-memory Quartz JobStore; no Docker service is needed. Prefer a small ApplicationContextRunner test that registers a simple JobDetail/Trigger or verifies SchedulerFactoryBean/Scheduler creation, and ensure the Spring context or scheduler is closed after each run. Avoid switching to spring.quartz.job-store-type=jdbc unless the test also supplies an embedded DataSource and schema initialization.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact also contains optional actuator endpoint classes; endpoint-specific coverage may require spring-boot-actuator, but core Quartz scheduler auto-configuration coverage does not.\",\n    \"Quartz starts scheduler threads when auto-startup is enabled, so tests must close the context or scheduler to avoid hangs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04e9419ef8ccb5e1016a3fe4ac72908195842937d904d7a672\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1609, "output": 1422, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37847, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782572184426, "responseId": "resp_04e9419ef8ccb5e1016a3fe4992f34819595ea88ca176edbf8"}, "toolResults": []}
